a;-hydroxylation and 17,20-lyase transformation. This leads to the transformation of pregnenolone to 17-OH-pregnenolone and 17-OH-pregnenolone to DHEA, respectively (Burris-Hiday &amp; Scott, 2021; Miller &amp; Auchus, 2011, 2019; Peng et al., 2019; Wr&oacute;bel et al., 2023). If either of these reactions are inhibited, it can lead to decreased DHEA levels.", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:16:38 +0000 2026"}